-- Mexico Stocks: Cemex, Penoles, Wal-Mart de Mexico Shares Rise
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-01-18T19:53:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/mexico-stocks-cemex-penoles-wal-mart-de-mexico-shares-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:33 p.m. in Mexico City.  The IPC  index  rose 1.4 percent to 37,101.79.  Mexican stocks followed U.S. equities higher as confidence
among homebuilders topped economists’ forecasts and Goldman
Sachs Group Inc. jumped after its earnings report.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO)  , the largest cement maker in the
Americas, rose 6.5 percent to 8.15 pesos.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB 
(WALMEXV MM),  Latin America ’s largest retailer, added 1.5
percent to 37.73 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, gained 2.3 percent to 620.90 pesos. Silver
futures for March delivery rose as much as 1.5 percent on the
Comex.  To contact the reporter on this story:
